                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.48/95: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The High Commissioner at Constantinople</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bristol</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-09-14T13:00:00+03:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 14, 1922—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>183. Following delayed telegram from Davis repeated for information of Department
                    and American Red Cross: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Eleventh. In interview today with Noureddin Pasha, commander of Turkish
                            forces Smyrna, placed before him in name of American committee your
                            views regarding restoration of refugees to their homes immediately under
                            full protection to life and property. He replied that complete
                            destruction of country by retreating Greek Army made this forever
                            impossible and refugees must leave country or be taken away, frankly
                            stating safety of life could not be assured. Believe this is final
                            decision Nationalist Government as solution of race problem. This opens
                            large question with many pros and cons and do not feel prepared to
                            comment at this time but it makes certain the need of large relief work
                            here. Representatives of American institutions and business men
                            cooperating splendidly and immediate needs of refugees being covered.
                            Davis.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bristol</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
